bug.author: AlexDBlack
bug.summary: ND4J: SimpleFileVisitor not available on Android?
bug.description:
Not sure why we've never seen this before, but it might be worth looknig into this... From stack trace here: <denchmark-link:https://github.com/deeplearning4j/deeplearning4j/issues/6608>https://github.com/deeplearning4j/deeplearning4j/issues/6608</denchmark-link>
<denchmark-code>Rejecting re-init on previously-failed class java.lang.Class<org.nd4j.versioncheck.VersionCheck$1>: java.lang.NoClassDefFoundError: Failed resolution of: Ljava/nio/file/SimpleFileVisitor; at void org.nd4j.versioncheck.VersionCheck.checkVersions() (VersionCheck.java:89) at void org.nd4j.linalg.factory.Nd4j.initWithBackend(org.nd4j.linalg.factory.Nd4jBackend) (Nd4j.java:5458) at void org.nd4j.linalg.factory.Nd4j.initContext() (Nd4j.java:5447) </denchmark-code>

comments.comment: It's available from Android 8.0 onwards so I wouldn't worry about it too much: <denchmark-link:https://developer.android.com/reference/java/nio/file/SimpleFileVisitor>https://developer.android.com/reference/java/nio/file/SimpleFileVisitor</denchmark-link>

Android 8.0 was is only 13 months old (general availability) according to my quick search - is that really enough for backward compatibility? <denchmark-link:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Android_Oreo>https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Android_Oreo</denchmark-link>
8.0 minimum cuts out the majority of users, if this is to be believed... <denchmark-link:https://developer.android.com/about/dashboards/>https://developer.android.com/about/dashboards/</denchmark-link>
Wait, that's in the version check? Did you change that recently?
Strange, I guess we should at least add a catch block there and not fail in the event that this class doesn't load.
